<P>
   COXNET FOCUS 0916: FINAL DAYS OF LIFE -- How will you spend your
last days? In a hospital, or at home? Suffering through surgeries,
or quietly accepting your fate? Most of us don't like to think
about death In a four-part, six-hour series on PBS, commentator
Bill Moyers brought the subject to the nation's consciousness by
interviewing patients, families and doctors determined to improve
end-of-life care. Here, we introduce you to three people who are
dying, and they tell us what it's like. (Kalajian /Palm Beach Post)
Art includes a 3-column color photo of an elderly couple, a
2-column color photo of an elderly couple and a 2-column color
photo of a middle-age couple.
