</P>
<P>
   FASHION-LEATHER _As leather's become one of the new centerpieces
of fall dressing in the latest textures, cuts and colors we devote
centerpiece space to the purchasing, care and cleaning of all
things hide. (Johnson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   HIPPS _ Move over Lane Bryant. Make room for Hipps, the new,
upscale boutique for women who have them. The shop, owned by
Cynthia K. Johnson, a former fulton county assistant DA and her
partner, Marie Gant Powell, a former merchandiser for Vanity Fair,
is like a Saks Fifth Avenue for full figured women who wear sizes
14 to 24. With prices ranging from $95 for a shell to $1,500 for an
evening gown, Hipps isn't cheap. But shopping there is an
experience. The boutique is a gallery with paintings, whimiscal
art, makeup, aromatherapy products and self-help books. (Hill,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   ELIAN-TV _ By now, I'm sure, you know Elian Gonzalez's life
story just as well as you know your own. A teddy bear cute
5-year-old boy makes his way to the United States from Cuba in a
small boat with his mom and other relatives and friends. But
Elian's mom, along with ten other would-be immigrants, dies when
the boat sinks. Elian, however, survives by clinging to a tiny
inner tube for two days in shark-infested waters. He's eventually
found three miles off the coast of Fort Lauderdale by two
fishermen. (Thompson, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
