   WITH: HORSES AND WOMEN -- There comes a time in almost every
girl's life when she falls in love with horses. This phenomenon,
this quality of nature, is easily observable, but Melissa Holbrook
Pierson more than observes it; she muses on it to deep and lyrical
effect in ``Dark Horses and Black Beauties,'' her new collection of
slender and delicate essays on horses and women. (Bernstein, N.Y.
