<P>
   BOOKS-HUMPHREYS _ Josephine Humphreys had complete crop failure
in her Sullivan's Island garden this summer, but all was not lost.
The caterpillars that ate her dill emerged as Monarch butterflies
and she finally finished ``Nowhere Else on Earth,'' her historical
novel about star-crossed Lumbee Indian lovers after nearly a decade
of writing and research. (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
